docs.lead_paragraph: TO judge from this absorbing book by Lady Russell, truth is not only stranger than fiction, but more romantic than romance. The volume contains close upon a score of stories, in each of which one or more of the characters are, as she tells us in her "foreword," nearly or remotely connected with her family.
